---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="701am — Earned Media for Nursing Staffing Agencies"
  description="The hospital already trusts a name. It just isn't yours — yet. Earned media that makes a nursing staffing agency the one directors of nursing recognise before the bid."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Industries', url: '/industries' },
    { name: 'Nursing Staffing Agencies' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════ HERO ════ -->
  <section class="hero" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-rays" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-overline">
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
        Industries · For nursing staffing agencies
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The hospital already trusts a name.<br />
        It just isn't yours — <em>yet.</em>
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        Travel nurses sign with the agency they have heard of. So do the directors of nursing who approve the contracts. <em>In a market of ten thousand interchangeable firms, the one that gets quoted on the shortage becomes the one they remember.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-cluster">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/discovery">
          Book a sunrise call
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#method">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="cta-fine">Thirty minutes. No deck. No pitch. No charge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ PRESS STRIP — the trades hospitals read ════ -->
  <section class="press-strip" aria-label="Where the staffing story gets told">
    <div class="press-inner">
      <p class="press-label">
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
        Where the staffing story gets told
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
      </p>
      <div class="press-logos">
        <span class="press-logo press-condensed">BECKER'S HOSPITAL REVIEW</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-italic">Modern Healthcare</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-condensed">STAFFING INDUSTRY ANALYSTS</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-italic">Fierce Healthcare</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-roman">HealthLeaders</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE FIRST TRUTH ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 01 · The first truth</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">A commodity market<br /><em>rewards the name it knows.</em></h2>
      <div class="body">
        <p class="dropcap">
          From the outside, every nursing staffing agency looks the same. Same job boards, same pay packages, same promise of people who care. A travel nurse weighing four offers — a hospital VP weighing four vendors — cannot tell you apart on the spec sheet. So they fall back on the only thing that breaks the tie: <em>which name have I heard of before.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="aphorism">The shortlist is written before the bid</div>

        <p>
          That recognition is not bought with another job-board ad. It is built when a reporter writing about the nursing shortage calls <strong>you</strong> for the number — when your CEO is the one quoted on the new staffing-ratio law — when a director of nursing reads your name in the trade journal she already trusts, the morning before your rep ever calls.
        </p>

        <p>
          The data is sitting in your ATS right now. Fill rates by specialty. Time-to-place in the rural markets no one else will touch. What your nurses actually say about burnout in the exit surveys. Each one is a story a healthcare reporter is hunting for and <em>cannot get from your competitors.</em> Most agencies file it under operations. The leaders recognise it as the most valuable un-pitched story in the building.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — THE LEDGER ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy ledger-section">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 02 · The ledger</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What an earned placement <em>does for a desk.</em></h2>

      <div class="ledger-grid">
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">18</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Placements earned</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">In a single quarter</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">3</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Trade-tier outlets</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Becker's · Modern Healthcare · SIA</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">1</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Un-ignorable number</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Pulled from the ATS</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ledger-prose">
        <p>
          The pattern repeats across operators in commoditised service markets. We spend the first weeks finding the number no competitor can claim — a regional gap, a specialty crisis, a retention figure that contradicts the headline — and the rest placing it where buyers already read. <em>The specialty changes. The mechanism does not.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Illustrative of the pattern. Client specifics confidential. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE METHOD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="method">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <p class="proclamation-hinge">
        The office holds the same two articles, whatever the industry on the masthead —
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 03 · The method</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2 h2-dark">Two things. Done <em>without compromise.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-dark body-center">
        <p>
          We do not write your blog or run your social calendar. We build the conditions under which a director of nursing already knows your agency before your rep dials. <em>The method fits on a single page, and it does not bend for the vertical.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <article class="doc">
        <header class="doc-header">
          <div class="doc-stamp">★ Tenets of the office ★</div>
          <h3 class="doc-title">The Two Articles of Earned Authority</h3>
          <p class="doc-sub">Adopted at sunrise. Held for the staffing desk.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. i</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Find the angle inside your fill data.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              Buried in your placement records is one true sentence about the nursing shortage that no competitor can claim and no editor can refuse. <em>It is almost never the thing in your sales deck.</em> We sit with your operations until we find it, and then we sharpen it until it cuts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. ii</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Place it where hospitals already read.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              A statistic in a press release is still a press release. We do the unglamorous work — the research, the pitch, the follow-up — until the right reporter at <em>Becker's</em> or <em>Modern Healthcare</em> runs the story. Then we do it again, until your name is the answer when a hospital asks who understands the shortage.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-sig">
          <p class="doc-sig-line">— 701am, est. at sunrise</p>
          <div class="doc-sig-title">Office of Earned Media</div>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-wax">7:01</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — THE WORK ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="work">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 04 · The work</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Three engagements.<br /><em>Built for the desk.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          Three ways the office goes to work on a staffing agency. <em>Pick the one that fits the quarter you are in.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="stamp-rule">
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-time">7:01</div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="eng-grid">
        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">i.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement I · The fastest</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Mine the <em>shortage story.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            We turn your existing fill-rate and retention data into a single reporter-ready angle on the nursing shortage — the number a healthcare editor cannot get anywhere else.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Data audit of your ATS</li>
            <li>One un-ignorable thesis</li>
            <li>Reporter-ready memo</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">ii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement II · The campaign</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Own the <em>quarter's narrative.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            A sustained placement campaign across the trades your buyers read. Your CEO becomes the named source on staffing ratios, travel-nurse pay, and the policy fights that decide your market.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Pitch · place · follow-up</li>
            <li>Becker's · Modern Healthcare · SIA</li>
            <li>Executive positioning</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">iii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement III · The engine</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Arm your <em>internal team.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            The earned-media skills your marketing lead can run themselves — pitch craft, journalist research, the angle-finder — tuned to the healthcare staffing beat and built to outlast any one campaign.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Earned-media playbook</li>
            <li>Healthcare press list</li>
            <li>Repeatable, in-house</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ FOUNDER NOTE ════ -->
  <section class="founder-note">
    <div class="founder-inner reveal">
      <p class="founder-eyebrow">
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
        A note from the office
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <blockquote class="founder-quote">
        There are a thousand agencies promising your nurses a better package. There are perhaps a handful who can get a hospital to recognise your name before the bid. <em>We are built for the second problem.</em> If that is the one keeping you up, the sunrise call is free.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="founder-sig">
        <span class="founder-name">— David</span>
        <span class="founder-time">at 7:01</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § — FROM THE FIELD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — From the field</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What the desk <em>hears back.</em></h2>

      <div class="field-grid">
        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">“</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            They found a number in our placement data we had been sitting on for years. Six weeks later our CEO was quoted in Becker's on the rural nursing gap. Two health systems called us first.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">VP of Growth</span>
            <span class="field-role">Regional travel-nurse agency</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">“</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            We had spent a fortune on ads no nurse remembered. One earned story in a journal our hospital clients actually read did more for the pipeline than the whole paid quarter.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Founder</span>
            <span class="field-role">Per-diem staffing firm</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">“</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            What I paid for was placements. What I got was a thesis for how we talk about the shortage. Every pitch we run now is downstream of that first call.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">CMO</span>
            <span class="field-role">National healthcare staffing platform</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Names withheld where confidentiality required. Words unchanged. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ CTA ════ -->
  <CtaBanner
    eyebrow="The work begins at 7:01"
    heading="Ready to be the agency <em>they already know?</em>"
    body="Thirty minutes. We listen, find the angle hiding in your fill data, and tell you straight whether we can make your agency impossible for a hospital to ignore."
    primaryLabel="Book a sunrise call"
    primaryHref="/discovery"
    secondaryLabel="Or read the field manual"
    secondaryHref="/legend-maker"
  />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── ENGAGEMENTS — mirrors the index "offers" three-up ─────── */
  .eng-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .eng-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .eng-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f3-size);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-tier {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.12;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .eng-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .eng-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .eng-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--x4) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .eng-list li {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding: var(--x5) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--x4);
    counter-increment: eng;
  }
  .eng-list { counter-reset: eng; }
  .eng-list li::before {
    content: counter(eng, lower-roman) ".";
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 12px;
    min-width: 1.4em;
  }

  /* ─────── FROM THE FIELD — mirrors the index testimonial cards ─────── */
  .field-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--x3);
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
  }
  .field-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5)) var(--x2);
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .field-mark {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 0.5;
    height: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .field-quote {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    flex: 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .field-by {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: var(--x4);
  }
  .field-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    color: var(--claret);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .field-role {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--x5);
  }

  /* ─────── RESPONSIVE ─────── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .eng-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .field-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
